{{ 'dev-fibre-cta.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{%- comment -%}
  Section: "Fibre CTA" (dev name `fibre-cta`).
  Figma layer: "Frame 6564" — desktop 45086:10217 (1440x530), mobile 44821:6854 (375x495).
  Page: Tree-Fibre (NOT the homepage).

  No JS: the Brief's Interactivity section is "none". The CTA is a real anchor, exactly as it is
  in the mobile export (the button component is wrapped in a cursor-pointer link). There is no
  slider, accordion, tab, sticky or scroll behaviour, so no dev-fibre-cta.js exists.

  No blocks: the Brief is explicit — nothing in this section repeats, and the single CTA button
  is a design-system component instance that appears exactly once. It is Section Settings, not a
  block. Do not invent a block type here.

  No inline SVG: this section has zero vector assets. .figma-assets/fibre-cta/ does not exist
  because asset-prep found nothing to export — the only artwork is the raster card photo.

  BACKGROUND — read before "fixing" this.
  `--bg` (#FCF5E3, Cream/100) is the CARD's background, not the section's. The section root is
  deliberately TRANSPARENT so the page background shows through the 64px side gutters and the
  80px top spacer — same convention as dev-tree-fibre-intro on this page. Painting --bg on the
  root would flood those gutters cream and fail the pixel diff outright.

  PADDING-BOTTOM IS 0 ON BOTH BREAKPOINTS — confirmed by exact node math, not inferred:
    desktop 530 = 80 (top spacer) + 450 (card), no remainder
    mobile  495 = 48 (top padding) + 447 (card), no remainder
  The visual gap after this section comes from the NEXT section's own top spacer, per this
  file's spacer-component convention. Do not add a bottom padding value that isn't in the design.

  MOBILE SIDE PADDING IS 16px, NOT 32px.
  Figma's generated class for the mobile wrapper says px-[32px], but the card's own bounding box
  (x=16, width=343, inside a 375 frame) requires 16px each side: (375 - 343) / 2 = 16. Absolute
  node coordinates beat a generated class name. QA asserts 16px.

  TWO IMAGE CROPS, NOT ONE IMAGE SCALED.
  Figma holds genuinely different crops of the same photograph: desktop 1500x1000 landscape,
  mobile 1001x1500 portrait. Both are in Shopify Files. Art-directed with <picture> + a media
  <source> so exactly one file is fetched per viewport — not two images toggled with display:none.
  If the merchant leaves the mobile picker empty it falls back to the desktop crop.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .fibre-cta {
    /* Brand params (Brief → Brand Params table). Faces are loaded by snippets/dev-brand-fonts.liquid. */
    --container-max: 1312px;
    --section-px: 64px;
    --section-px-m: 16px;

    /* Typography — desktop */
    --font-heading-size: 32px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;
    --font-body-size: 16px;
    --font-body-weight: 700;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;

    /* Typography — mobile: taken from the Mobile artboard (Mobile/Title 3), not a scale factor. */
    --font-heading-size-m: 24px;

    /* Spacing — desktop. The text column's padding is asymmetric in Figma (32 vertical,
       119 horizontal); it is NOT a uniform tier, so it does not collapse into --spacing-*. */
    --spacing-sm: 16px;
    --spacing-md: 24px;
    --card-pad-y: 32px;
    --card-pad-x: 119px;

    /* Spacing — mobile: card padding collapses to a uniform 24px and the text gap drops to 16px. */
    --card-pad-m: 24px;

    /* Mobile top spacer is 48px against a desktop 80px. Scaling the merchant's own padding_top
       keeps that relationship intact if they change it. 80 * 0.6 = 48. */
    --pt-scale-m: 0.6;

    /* Button text is Neutral/700 — the same token as the body text colour, not a separate
       merchant setting. Fixed relationship in the design. */
    --button-color: var(--color);
    --button-pad-y: 12px;
    --button-pad-x: 18px;

    /* Layout / decoration */
    --radius-card: 32px;
    --radius-button: 60px;

    /* The image's own aspect is what sets the card height at each breakpoint:
       desktop 656x450 inside a 1312 card; mobile 343x250 inside a 343 card. */
    --media-ratio: 656 / 450;
    --media-ratio-m: 343 / 250;
  }
</style>

{%- liquid
  # richtext: already-safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it. The <p> wrapper is unwrapped so
  # the copy stays inline inside the <h2> (same idiom as dev-featured-product).
  assign heading_html = section.settings.heading | remove: '<p>' | remove: '</p>'

  assign image = section.settings.image
  assign image_mobile = section.settings.image_mobile
  if image_mobile == blank
    assign image_mobile = image
  endif

  assign image_alt = section.settings.alt_text
  if image_alt == blank
    assign image_alt = image.alt
  endif
  assign image_alt = image_alt | default: '' | escape

  assign m_343 = image_mobile | image_url: width: 343
  assign m_500 = image_mobile | image_url: width: 500
  assign m_686 = image_mobile | image_url: width: 686
  assign m_1001 = image_mobile | image_url: width: 1001
  assign mobile_srcset = m_343 | append: ' 343w, ' | append: m_500 | append: ' 500w, ' | append: m_686 | append: ' 686w, ' | append: m_1001 | append: ' 1001w'

  assign button_label = section.settings.button_label
-%}

<div
  class="fibre-cta"
  style="
    --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
    --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --accent: {{ section.settings.accent_color }};
    --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
  "
>
  <div class="fibre-cta__inner">
    <div class="fibre-cta__card">
      {%- if image != blank -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Source fills are 1500x1000 (desktop crop) and 1001x1500 (mobile crop), so those are the
          largest useful widths. Rendered with object-fit: cover — the Brief says explicitly not to
          reproduce Figma's literal crop-offset percentages.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <div class="fibre-cta__media">
          <picture class="fibre-cta__picture">
            <source
              media="(max-width: 768px)"
              srcset="{{ mobile_srcset }}"
              sizes="calc(100vw - 32px)"
            >
            {{
              image
              | image_url: width: 1500
              | image_tag:
                loading: 'lazy',
                widths: '400, 600, 800, 1000, 1200, 1500',
                sizes: '(min-width: 1440px) 656px, (min-width: 769px) calc(50vw - 64px), calc(100vw - 32px)',
                alt: image_alt,
                class: 'fibre-cta__image'
            }}
          </picture>
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="fibre-cta__content">
        {%- if section.settings.heading != blank -%}
          <h2 class="fibre-cta__heading">{{ heading_html }}</h2>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if button_label != blank -%}
          {%- render 'dev-button',
            variant: 'filled',
            label: button_label | escape,
            link: section.settings.button_link,
            class: 'fibre-cta__button'
          -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Fibre CTA",
  "tag": "section",
  "presets": [{ "name": "Fibre CTA" }],
  "settings": [
    { "type": "header", "content": "Content" },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "info": "Use a line break to split the heading across lines.",
      "default": "<p>A single, unique and plant-based fibre – redefining what a duvet can do.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image",
      "label": "Image",
      "info": "Landscape crop. Shown beside the text on desktop and tablet."
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image_mobile",
      "label": "Mobile image",
      "info": "Optional. The design uses a different, taller crop below 768px. Falls back to the image above if left empty."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "alt_text",
      "label": "Image alt text",
      "info": "Optional. Falls back to the alt text set on the image in Files."
    },
    { "type": "text", "id": "button_label", "label": "Button label", "default": "Trial Our Duvet" },
    { "type": "url", "id": "button_link", "label": "Button link" },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Colors" },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "background_color",
      "label": "Card background",
      "info": "The cream card. The section itself stays transparent so the page background shows through.",
      "default": "#FCF5E3"
    },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "text_color",
      "label": "Text color",
      "info": "Also used for the button label.",
      "default": "#333333"
    },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "accent_color",
      "label": "Accent color",
      "info": "The button background, and focus outlines.",
      "default": "#A8CF78"
    },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Spacing" },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "label": "Padding top",
      "info": "Scales to 60% of this on mobile (80px → 48px), matching the Mobile artboard.",
      "default": 80
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "label": "Padding bottom",
      "info": "The design has no bottom spacer — the next section's own top spacer carries the gap.",
      "default": 0
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
